# PawPal Website — AI Coding Rules
# This file is read by Cursor AI to enforce project conventions.
# See DEVELOPER_GUIDE.md at the monorepo root for the complete reference.

## Architecture
- This is a **Next.js 16** app using the App Router with React 19 and TypeScript.
- Pages are Server Components by default. Add `'use client'` only when needed.
- Extract interactive parts to separate client components (e.g., `HomeClientParts.tsx`).

## Supabase Client Usage (CRITICAL)
- **Server Components / API Routes**: Use `supabaseServer` from `@/lib/supabaseServer`.
- **Client Components**: Use `supabase` from `@/lib/supabase`.
- NEVER use raw `fetch()` with Supabase REST URL. Always use the Supabase JS client.
- NEVER construct SQL queries via string concatenation.

## Styling
- Use **Tailwind CSS v4** for styling. No inline styles unless absolutely necessary.
- Follow the existing design system: warm colors (`amber`, `emerald`), glassmorphism, rounded corners.
- Background: `bg-[#fffdf9]`, text: `text-gray-800`.

## Components
- Animations use `framer-motion`. Prefer `motion.div` with fade/slide variants.
- Icons use `lucide-react`. Do not mix icon libraries.
- 3D Globe uses `react-globe.gl` + `three`. Heavy — only load on globe pages.

## Security
- API keys go in `.env.local` (git-ignored). Access via `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_*`.
- NEVER expose server-side secrets to client components.
- `.env.local` is already in `.gitignore`.

## SEO
- Every page must have a `<title>` and meta description.
- Use semantic HTML (`<section>`, `<article>`, `<nav>`).
- Single `<h1>` per page.

## Performance
- Prefer Server Components for static content (zero JS shipped to browser).
- Lazy-load heavy components (Globe, Maps) with `dynamic()`.
- Images: use `next/image` for optimization.
